    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 7000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - FENDER EXTENSIONS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="5">
        <title>FENDER EXTENSIONS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fender Extension - Remove</title>
            <para>The fender extensions are part of the body splash protection system. The wheel well openings in the
                fender extensions have been designed to provide splash and spray protection. These protect the lower
                front of the cab from splash and road debris kicked up by the front tires, and it also keeps the step
                cleaner (
                <hotlnk document="s09007_9.xml" xrefid="f0900709">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release hood latches on each side of the hood and tilt the hood assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to Figure 44 for all items in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the fender extension mounting bolts and nuts on the fender extension assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900744">Items 1, 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the three mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900745">Item 3</hotlnk>) on the rear surface of the fender extension.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the stud mounting nut from the fender extension mounting stud.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fender extension
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900743">(Figure 43, Item 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow same procedure to remove opposite side fender extension.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900743" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900743.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Fender Extension (Driver Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CAB STEP</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MUD GUARD</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FENDERETTES</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HOOD LATCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0900744" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900744.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 44. Fender Extension Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HOOD LATCH MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FENDER EXTENSION MOUNTING STUD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fender Extension - Install</title>
            <para>With hood in the tilted position, locate the fender extension mounting stud on the cab lower forward
                structure (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900744">Figure 44, Item 3</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900745" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900745.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. Fender Extension Install</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION TO CAB MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING STUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FENDER EXTENSION TO LOWER CAB MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the fender extension mounting hole on the mounting stud (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900745">Figure 45, Item 2</hotlnk>), install mounting nut. Hand tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the mounting holes on the fender extension with the mounting holes on the lower
                    cab structure.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install mounting bolts and lock washers and tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the mounting nut on the fender extension mounting stud.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the mounting bolts. Torque to 50 to 55 lbf-ft (68 to 75 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Lower Hood Latch Assembly - Remove</title>
            <para>The hood latching mechanism consists of two parts. The lower lock portion of the latching mechanism is
                located on the fender extension assembly (Figure 46, Item 1).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900746" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900746.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Lower Hood Latch Assembly (Fender Extension)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOWER HOOD HATCH ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LATCH ASSEMBLY MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BOLT MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. LATCH ASSEMBLY LOCK NUTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Hood latch clip removal:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release hood latch both sides and tilt hood forward.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate mounting bolts, hex nuts and washers, loosen and remove.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove hatch clip assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow same procedure on opposite side for lower latch clip assembly removal.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Upper Hood Latch - Install</title>
            <figure id="f0900747" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900747.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Upper Hood Latch Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. VALANCE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING BOLTS AND FLAT WASHERS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. UPPER HOOD LATCHING ATTACHMENT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FENDER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood assembly forward and locate the latch clip mounting holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900744">Figure 44, Item 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the latch clip on the fender extension aligning the mounting holes with the
                    holes in the fender extension.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert mounting bolts and flat washers through the latch clip assembly and fender
                    assembly mounting holes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the hex nuts and lock washers on the mounting bolts and tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque to 34 to 38 lbf-ft (46 to 51 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
